Tradicted Trading Journal is a free offline-first desktop trading
journal for Linux. Features include a trade log, analytics dashboard
with equity curve and performance metrics, a journal with calendar
view and psychology tags, multiple portfolio support, and a built-in
trading plan checklist.
All data is stored locally with no account required.

After installation, the AppImage requires FUSE to run. Make sure the
fuse kernel module is loaded:

  modprobe fuse

No other dependencies are required.
